This paper proposes a model for text generation using a variational autoencoder (VAE) with a Gaussian mixture model (GMM) prior parametrized by a neural topic module. The model is learned jointly with a VAE-based neural sequence module and uses invertible Householder transformations to increase flexibility during inference. Given the focus on natural language processing and machine learning, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of VAEs and neural networks also suggests potential relevance to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the use of invertible transformations may also suggest relevance to sub-category cs.CV (Computer Vision), which often uses similar techniques for image processing.
